Moegamat Shafiek Khan allegedly underdeclared his income between 2008 and 2011. CAPE TOWN - A man accused of scamming Sars out of R3.1 million is expected to appear in the Bellville Magistrates Court on Wednesday. Moegamat Shafiek Khan allegedly underdeclared his income between 2008 and 2011. He has been on the run since then, until earlier in September when investigators nabbed him. The Hawks’ Lloyd Ramovha said: “A warrant of arrest was issued against him following a fraud case that was registered in 2011, he was then arrested on Friday and made a brief court appearance on the same day. "The matter was postponed to today for a bail application.”